crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is a sample of the Babuk ransomware. It encrypts files on local drives and accessible network shares, appending the '.babyk' extension to them. Key malicious behaviors include creating a mutex 'babuk_v3', terminating a hardcoded list of processes and services to ensure unimpeded encryption, and deleting Volume Shadow Copies via the command 'vssadmin.exe delete shadows /all /quiet'. The ransomware drops a note named 'How To Restore Your Files.txt' which contains the Tor C2 URL 'http://babukq4e2p4wu4iq[.]onion/login.php' and explicitly identifies itself as 'BABUK LOCKER'.
